Extract Insecure App Configurations
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Analyze AndroidManifest.xml files to identify security misconfigurations
Extract hardcoded credentials from mobile application configuration files
Develop Python scripts to automate security assessment of mobile apps
Identify common mobile application security vulnerabilities
Generate security assessment reports for mobile applications
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic understanding of Android application architecture and XML structure
Fundamental Python programming skills
Familiarity with Linux command-line operations
Basic knowledge of mobile application security concepts
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides Linux-based cloud machines for this lab. Click Start Lab to access your pre-configured environment with all necessary tools pre-installed.

